-- South African Stocks Index Closes at Five-Month High: BHP, Massmart Move
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-09-27T15:40:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/south-african-equities-bhp-billiton-massmart-shares-move.html
South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index  closed at its highest level since April 26,
advancing 244.65, or 0.9 percent, to 28,959.42 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg. The following were among the most active
stocks in the South African market today.  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ) rose the most in two weeks,
advancing 3.63 rand, or 1.7 percent, to 223.75 rand. The world’s
largest mining company reported it had been granted early
termination of the mandatory waiting period in connection with
its offer to buy Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc. BHP also
approved the Macedon Gas development in Western Australia.  Massmart Holdings Ltd.  (MSM SJ) rose to the highest level
since at least July 2000, advancing 14.25 rand, or 11 percent,
to 149 rand. South Africa’s biggest food and general goods
wholesaler said it received a non-binding proposal from Wal-Mart
Stores Inc. to buy the company for 148 rand a share.        Merafe Resources Ltd.  (MRF SJ) rose the first day in four
trading sessions, advancing 2 cents, or 1.4 percent, to 1.46
rand. The company, which is in a ferrochrome joint venture with
Xstrata Plc, said the European benchmark price for the metal has
been settled at $1.30 per pound.  To contact the reporter on this story:
